p0001 = "ORDER FOR THE ORDINATION OF A PRESBYTER"
p0002 = "After the completion if the Cherubikon, the one who is to be ordained Presbyter stands on the solea, two Deacons take the candidate on either side [to the middle of the church, with one hand on his neck and with the other holding his hands; and they bow him as low as possible. One Deacon says Give the order. They bring him forward and bow him down again; and another Deacon says: Give the order.] They bring him near the Holy Doors and bow him low before the Bishop, who is seated on his small throne in front of the Altar. The Archdeacon says: Give the order, Holy Master. Then they let him go and two Presbyters, the first and second in rank, come from the Sanctuary and take the one who is to be ordained Presbyter, who is standing on the Solea, and bring him into the Sanctuary, circling the Altar as they sing the following Troparia[, which are repeated by the Singers]:"
